title: Inter-Party Relationships
new-page: true
view-if: year <= 1932 and inter_party_relationships_timer <= 0
tags: party_affairs
is-card: true
on-arrival: month_actions += 1; inter_party_relationships_timer = 6;
card-image: img/electionposters.jpg
max-visits: 12
#subtitle: Building relations with the other political parties of Germany.

= Inter-Party Relationships

The SPD cannot govern by itself yet. Because we do not have an electoral majority, we need the support of other parties. Recently, our governments have consisted of the Weimar Coalition of the SPD, Center, and Democratic parties. We can reach out and build additional connections with these parties, or perhaps we can stand alone.

- @liberals: Strengthen our bonds with the left-liberal German Democratic Party and conservative-liberal German People's Party.
- @center: Strengthen our bonds with the Catholic Center Party.
- @kpd: Work towards repairing relationships with the Communist Party.
- @spd_alone: The SPD can stand alone for now.
- @easy_discard


@kpd
subtitle: -1 resources
choose-if: resources >= 1
unavailable-subtitle: Not enough resources.
on-arrival: resources -= 1; kpd_inter_party_seen += 1
go-to: kpd_blutmai if blutmai = 1; kpd_1 if blutmai = 0 and kpd_coalition_success = 0 and (kpd_relation < 40 or kpd_rectified_history = 1); kpd_rectification_of_history if kpd_relation >= 40 and kpd_rectified_history = 0; kpd_2 if kpd_coalition_success = 1 and kpd_rectified_history = 1

@kpd_1
on-arrival: kpd_relation += 6*(1 - dissent); communist_coalition += 1 if kpd_inter_party_seen <= 1; reformist_dissent += 2; z_relation -= 2; dvp_relation -= 3

The Left Esers are suspicious of our overtures, especially their Bolshevik faction, who persist in calling us "petty-bourgeois". However, connections are made at the grassroots and local levels.

@kpd_rectification_of_history

One stumbling block for our relations with the far-left is our history of conflict, dating back to the party split. The PLSRI is especially contemptuous of us for cooperating with the PSR. They also blame us for the deaths of Lenin and Spiridnova, RSDRP and PSR leaders who were killed during the failed Bolshevik revolt.

For further improvements in PLSRI relations, it might be necessary to condemn the army, and hold some sort of commemoration for Lenin and Spiridnova.

- @yes_history: Yes, we must apologize for our past actions.
- @no_history: No, we have no need to apologize.

@yes_history
on-arrival: reformist_dissent += 12; reformist_strength -= 2; neorevisionist_dissent += 5; left_dissent -= 6; left_strength += 5; kpd_rectified_history = 1; z_relation -= 6; dvp_relation -= 6; ddp_relation -= 4; kpd_relation += 8*(1-dissent); coalition_dissent += 1

As part of normalizing relations with the PLSRI, we have to acknowledge the wrongdoings of our past. We have condemned the army, and have held public commemorations for those killed by troops during the uprisings.

This leads to tensions with the moderates and Economists within our party, and criticism from the conservative and liberal parties.

@no_history
on-arrival: kpd_relation -= 3

We have no need to apologize for the actions of the army and police; it is their fault for launching a violent insurrection and trying to overthrow democracy.


@kpd_2
on-arrival: kpd_relation += 8*(1 - dissent); communist_coalition += 1 if kpd_inter_party_seen <= 1; reformist_dissent += 2; z_relation -= 3; dvp_relation -= 3

After the success of the coalition government with the PLSRI, they are much more amenable to us.

@kpd_blutmai
on-arrival: kpd_relation += 3*(1 - dissent); reformist_dissent += 1

After the events of *Red Tuesday*, reconciling with the Communists is difficult, if not impossible. Nevertheless, we must try.

@center
subtitle: -1 resources
choose-if: resources >= 1
unavailable-subtitle: Not enough resources.
on-arrival: resources -= 1; z_relation += 2 if z_party_leader == "Joos"
go-to: center_op if z_in_government = 1 and spd_in_government = 0 and chancellor != "Brüning"; center_coalition if spd_in_government = 1 and z_in_government = 1; center_bruning if chancellor = "Brüning"

@center_op
on-arrival: z_relation += 5*(1 - dissent)

We are currently in opposition to the PSR-led government, but that does not preclude the general building of feelings of good will.

@center_coalition
on-arrival: z_relation += 8*(1 - dissent)

We are currently coalition partners with them, so improving relations comes naturally.

@center_bruning
on-arrival: z_relation += 5*(1 - dissent)

The semi-autocratic and conservative-leaning regime of Savinkov makes building friendly relations difficult, but not impossible.

@liberals
subtitle: -1 resources
choose-if: resources >= 1
unavailable-subtitle: Not enough resources.
on-arrival: resources -= 1; ddp_relation += 5*(1 - dissent)
go-to: dvp_loss

The Kadets have been one of our closest rivals through the course of the Republic, but we are not enemies. Perhaps reaching out to their left-wing of Progressives could help us? Even Müsavat has grown considerable less social-democratic in the past years too.

@dvp_loss
on-arrival: dvp_relation += 5*(1 - dissent)

Holding meetings with Müsavat is not unheard of, but is unlikely to go anywhere, especially following the expulsion of their socialist-wing back in 1925. The Kadet's left-wing is happy to hear from us, thankfully.

However, given the influence of Müsavat and the Kadets among the other minority- and liberal-leaning parties [? if president == "Hindenburg": and with President Hindenburg ?], it can still be helpful to influence them.

@spd_alone

Whether it is because we *cannot* or *will not*, we do not make ties with other parties at this moment.

- @return: Continue...
